                                         JOHANNESBURG - Twenty children have been injured after they were stung by bees at a school in Amazimtoti in KwaZulu-Natal. Paramedics say they arrived at the school on Monday afternoon and were lead to the hall where the children were waiting for medical attention. ER24's Russel Meiring said: “Upon close inspection, we discovered that 20 children aged between two and six had sustained several bee sting injuries. Fortunately, none of them required hospitalisation, they were handed over to guardians and teachers for further care.”